description:
While doing a set(PUT) and update (POST) operation in server metadata it accepts leading and trailing white space in key and value pairs .

Set Request :

URI: http://10.2.3.169:8774/v2/5a88678e1b9a4c1d9c44ccbaad108bdc/servers/069a060b-691f-445e-ae80-f7f6bf4d4b48/metadata

 {
  "metadata": {
    "key1   ":"  value1   ",
    " key2":  " value2  "
}
}

response : Status : 200 (OK)

{
"metadata": {
" key2": " value2 ",
"key1 ": " value1 "
}
}

Ideally white spaces should not be allowed and should be trimmed before set and update request.

